                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/961: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-30T11:00:00-06:00"
                            >October 30, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>136. Referring to the Legation’s telegram of October 29, 6 p.m. The amended note
                    has been received dated October 28th.</p>
                <p>I am now telegraphing the Legation in Honduras with insertion of the amendment
                    the summary of the text contained in the telegram of October 28, 7 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geissler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
